CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 25, 1965, p. 12A, reads: "Contenders - While the basketball team at Schenley High School is heavily honored to repeat as City League basketball champions, Fifth Avenue High may be a strong contender for championship honors The Fifth Avenue team is shown above.  Left to right, back row, Tom Hawkins, Paul Dunn, Gerald Bruce and Richard Brooks.  Front row, Clarence Youngblood, George Robinson, Coach Cupples, John Kinsel and Arthur Reynolds.  Missing from photo is Cleveland Edwards.  (Harris Photo)"
TitMainTitle: Fifth Avenue High School basketball team, kneeling from left: Clarence Youngblood, George Robinson, coach George Cupples, John Kinsel, Arthur Reynolds; standing: Tom Hawkins, Paul Dunn, Gerald Bruce, and Richard Brooks posed in gymnasium
